## 3) State Machines

### Schedule lifecycle

#### Draft

* Editable without employee notification.
* Can be created from import, copy-last-week, recurring template, AI draft, or manual edits.
* Allowed transitions:

  * draft -> published
  * draft -> archived
  * draft -> recalled (invalid; recalled only applies to previously published schedules)

#### Published

* Current live schedule visible to employees.
* Any material change creates an amendment record and a new version.
* Allowed transitions:

  * published -> amended
  * published -> recalled
  * published -> archived

#### Amended

* Live schedule with one or more approved changes after publish.
* May receive additional amendment versions.
* Allowed transitions:

  * amended -> amended
  * amended -> recalled
  * amended -> archived

#### Recalled

* Previously published date range temporarily withdrawn for manager revision.
* A recalled schedule is not a separate schedule; it is a live schedule temporarily pulled back.
* Allowed transitions:

  * recalled -> published
  * recalled -> archived

#### Archived

* Historical record.
* Read-only except audit/admin metadata.
* No further operational transitions.

### Shift lifecycle

* draft -> scheduled -> published
* published -> at_risk (callout received / issue detected)
* at_risk -> open (manager confirmation or automatic rules)
* open -> covered (accepted and assigned)
* open -> escalated (no fill found)
* covered -> amended notification path
* any live state -> cancelled

### Enrollment lifecycle

* not_invited -> invited
* invited -> opted_in
* invited -> opted_out
* opted_in -> opted_out
* opted_out -> opted_in (via START/UNSTOP or fresh consent flow)
* any state -> blocked / unreachable

### Coverage workflow lifecycle

* pending -> offering
* offering -> awaiting_manager_approval
* offering -> filled
* offering -> escalated
* awaiting_manager_approval -> filled
* awaiting_manager_approval -> escalated
* any active state -> cancelled

